Title: Jedda the Uncivilized
Writer: Charles Chauvel (screenplay by), Elsa Chauvel (screenplay by)
Actors: Rosalie Kunoth-Monks, Robert Tudawali, Betty Suttor, Paul Reynall
Plot: Set against the harsh natural surrounds of outback Northern Territory, Jedda captures a rare and honest glimpse into the heart and history of indigenous Australia. Young Jedda is caught between two cultures forbidden from learning about her indigenous heritage and never fully accepted by the other.
